<div align="center">
  <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4">Jason Rogan</font></p>
  <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="3">&nbsp;writer &nbsp;producer</font></p>
  <p align="left"><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="3">Jason Rogan 
    began producing through the collaboration on several projects with long time 
    friend Enrico Falconi. Working with Falcon Productions, he has executive produced 
    six of Falconi&#146;s short films, 1937 (2002), Original Black Poet (2003), Alsjeblieft (2005), No Turning Back (2006), and Brotherly Love (2009). </font></p>
  <p align="left"><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="3">The documentary currently in production, Robin 
    Nolan &#150; Experience, which spans 11 years in the life and career of a 
    Gypsy Jazz virtuoso guitarist from Amsterdam, marks his first efforts as a 
    co-producer on a feature film.</font></p>
  <p align="left"><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="3">Other projects include executive producing with  Mirror Mountain Pictures the South African films Tengers (2007) and Game of  Life (2009).<br>
    <br>
    In college, Jason studied engineering and management. Upon graduation 
  in 1993, with an eye at honing his management skills, he took a supervising position in a manufacturing plant. In 1994 he began working 
  with Internet technology and became a technical trainer and public speaker, 
  eventually managing the training programs of several large corporations. <br>
    <br>
    Jason is currently in development on two screenplays of his own, Now Boarding 
    and Love Death.<br>
    <br>
    Born and raised in New York City&#146;s Greenwich Village, Jason currently 
    splits his time living in NYC and Amsterdam, Holland.<br>
    <br>
    <br>
  </font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
